In a large saucepan, combine the first seven ingredients. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Gradually stir a small amount of eggs; return all to the pan. Bring to a gentle boil, stirring constantly. Remove form the heat. Stir in rice and vanilla. Pour into a greased 13-in. x 9-in. x 2-in. baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 375&deg, for 25-30 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Serve warm with ice cream if desired. Refrigerate leftovers.